This app has really impressed me, I'm a student getting to grips with the basics of C++ programming. So I recently picked up a copy of C++ Primer, and I've been reading it everywhere I go and writing up the exercises in Evernote, but I had no way to compile and check my code until I got home.   I tried Terminal IDE, and diligently worked through there tutorials only to discover that at the end of the C++ tutorial it states, C++ doesn't actually work, tell me if you can fix it.   Then I took a bash at AIDE & I wasn't impressed, overly complex, and it kept throwing Java at me, and a half dozen files when I just wanted to make a single source file and compile it. I just want something that lets me code!  So I took the dive and shelled out my 3 bucks and boy was it worth it, installed, downloaded GCC wrote a short 'Hello World', clicked compile, clicked run and it worked perfectly. It's just so intuitive.   The only negative thing I could say is that the error messages could be a little clearer, but then again there are error messages and they're understandable.   5/5 for ease of use, and for doing exactly what is says on the tin!

Compiler works without problems (you can also edit gcc command line arguments, like -std=c99 or -lSDL2), editor and terminal emulator are good, and installation of plug-ins is painless. One of the best life-hacks here on Play.

replyContent:
graphics.h is not a part of any standard, it is used in old Borland compilers only, that's why it isn't supported.
Use modern alternatives (like Qt or SDL)

One can easily be skeptical of the functionality of a mobile compiler. Naturally, it's impossible to expect access to certain utilities and conveniences. However, luxuries of a big name desktop bound compilers aside, this app does exactly what it should. It runs anything from the standard c/c++ library I could need, and doesn't come with any odd quirks to note. While I wouldn't use this to program any large creations, I can say it is the perfect utility for a programmer on the go.

I am a programmer with about $25 in my Google Wallet account. What do I do? Buy this brilliant app, of course!  Let me explain this to you: Having to carry my heavy, little-battery-life laptop around is a pain, not to mention it takes 5 minutes just to boot. However, my Android tablet is light, easy to carry around, and has 10+ hours of battery life. I am coding an OS from scratch, just a neat little project of mine. I have tried things like touchqode (touchqode is free, but touchqode pro is something around $9.), but it would never open or save my files, leading to hours of frustration. Everything just works in c4droid. This is not only fast, it's smart, too. Syntax highlighting, one of the greatest features (for me) in any IDE, even desktop IDEs, is awesome in c4droid.Not only that, but the GCC plugin is absolutely awesome.  If you have a buck fifty able to be spent on an app, GET THIS ONE!!!!!!
